    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "599ef77d_e471347b",
        "filename": "client/crash_report_database.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 274,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144624
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-08-09T21:09:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027d like Mark to chime in, but I think the forced state can just be a variant of Pending. I think it would greatly reduce the size of the change.",
      "revId": "96974a129a585fd073be8d3ae8d7598385e46545",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "599ef77d_c41f500f",
        "filename": "client/crash_report_database.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 274,
      "author": {
        "id": 1143760
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-08-09T21:17:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I\u0027d like Mark to chime in, but I think the forced state can just be a variant of Pending. I\n\u003e think it would greatly reduce the size of the change.\n\nI agree. In fact, this is how I envisioned it when we discussed it on the list: as a “bit” on the pending state. (The implementation may need to write it to disk as a distinct state enum value in the Windows implementation, but the “bit” is at least conceptually valid there.) crashpad-dev link: https://groups.google.com/a/chromium.org/d/msg/crashpad-dev/Qhap0DeRWD4/5XwnIrDgBwAJ.",
      "parentUuid": "599ef77d_e471347b",
      "revId": "96974a129a585fd073be8d3ae8d7598385e46545",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "99f6afe4_7dbc971d",
        "filename": "client/crash_report_database.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 274,
      "author": {
        "id": 1116265
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-08-10T17:43:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Do I understand right, that you prefer having some boolean like isForced in CrashReportDatabase::Report similar to isUploaded which is a bit on completed ?\n\nFor terminology:  other options I can suggest are isManualUpload, isOnDemandUpload (the terms we used in discussion) or  isUserEnforced, isUserRequested",
      "parentUuid": "599ef77d_c41f500f",
      "revId": "96974a129a585fd073be8d3ae8d7598385e46545",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "599ef77d_447b4055",
        "filename": "client/crash_report_database.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 344,
      "author": {
        "id": 1143760
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-08-09T21:08:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don’t think we ever want to do this. What you’re now calling “force” is an operation that should only ever be applied to single crash reports. That’s what should happen if the user is on about:crashes and decides “I want to upload this one report, but I don’t want to enable uploads for all reports.”\n\nWe wouldn’t want to bring all of these reports back to life and make them eligible for upload in one fell swoop. We certainly wouldn’t want to do that while circumventing the user’s upload-enabled preference.",
      "revId": "96974a129a585fd073be8d3ae8d7598385e46545",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "599ef77d_24783c56",
        "filename": "client/crash_report_database.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 351,
      "author": {
        "id": 1143760
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-08-09T21:08:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ditto here on the terminology. “Force report” doesn’t mean what you want it to mean.",
      "revId": "96974a129a585fd073be8d3ae8d7598385e46545",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
